scenes.label: *dummy1
texts: I finished setting up the app and created a backdoor exclusive to Nakano Symphonies.
...Yeah. I'm in. Gonna start looking it over.
I removed the wire from the carrianode.
Suddenly, the smell of strong perfume hit my nose.
The next moment, I felt someone's hand on my shoulder.
Momo was sat beside me, but she wasn't reaching out or anything, and Lime was still in the captain's seat.
Overcome with dread, I slowly turned around.

scenes.label: *load
texts: There was a train coming toward me.
%a20;Weren't we in a room just now? Was this an illusion? Why was I standing on tracks? Was this real? If it was, then I was about to...
Everything told me this was very, clearly real.

texts: The next thing I knew, I was lying beside the tracks.
Momo was on top of me, and I realized it was thanks to her that I was still alive.
I looked through the gaps between the railroad cars to see a man with a baffled look on his face.
Next to him was a woman I felt I'd seen before.
I squinted, and tried to jog my memory.
But the next moment, they were both gone.
We pulled each other up, hand in hand, then left the area.
I guess we couldn't see you 'cause of the network failure. I lost my connection to Lime too.
Did that woman take him away?
HUUUHHH?! WAS THAT "THE" JUNO?! FOR REAL?! NO WAY!
Right! The one Oz almost ran over!
I'd never seen her face before, so I didn't realize that was JUNO. Never would've guessed she was \#1 in the quest rankings.
So she's both wizard-tier and a real beauty! I thought the pics on the internet were fake!

texts: I checked for any signs someone had forced their way in, but there was nothing suggesting I'd been hacked.
Even the GPS logs were saying I'd instantly transported from the room to the tracks.
Bro, I didn't just pop up someplace else—I was also almost hit by a train!
How was I supposed to stay calm?
Seems JUNO is known for appearing out of nowhere and leaving without a trace.
And so far, not a single hacker has figured out how she does it.
So you're saying there's no point even thinking about it?
Beary-Airy b.2 is complete! Umm, it's b.2 because—
We're not firing it. We couldn't get the flight path.
What? Say it ain't so, spicy miso!
Fuckin' JUNO just had to get in my way.
I'm not lettin' that happen next time!
JUNO must've been the one who arrived before the Cyber Force Dolls last time. We had to figure out how to stop her getting in our way.
Cross, how did Lime's BMI look?
I thought I could overwrite the guidance data, but that doesn't seem realistic. It'd take days, and even then I'm not sure we'd succeed.
We'd actually have a better shot going with your crazy plan.
I guess we'll just have to get that flight path before JUNO shows up.
I checked the software I'd installed in the electronic lock for an alert that might tell me when she arrived.
I'd set it to go off when its security was bypassed.
The one who touched my shoulder must have been JUNO, right?
You moved at about 10:05. JUNO must've gotten in right before that.
There's no way she was in the room the whole time...right?
Considering she was a wizard-tier hacker, I guess she just erased the alert.
We entered the room a little before ten o'clock.
So we only have about five minutes to work with...
Setting up the backdoor took just over four minutes, but if we left right after that, we'd just be found by JUNO.
On the other hand, taking care of the backdoor later would give us less time to get the flight path.
Why don't you modify the customer data?
That must've been how JUNO found his address. If we change his data, we might buy ourselves a minute or two.
But where would we go in that time?
Lime had to play Garuda, so moving him around wouldn't be easy. Putting him on a graper was out of the question.
Thinking back, JUNO must've been the one behind the CANBUS hack in Shinjuku too.

scenes.label: *load2
texts: What sort of car would be secure...?
A police car or an armored vehicle, I guess.
Ah! Will you ask the CCO?
Yeah, the quests are cybercrimes. I'm sure they'll help out.
Police cars could go pretty fast too.
Okay. We know what to do now.
Thanks to Momo and Cross, I was starting to see the light at the end of the tunnel.
I had to avoid JUNO and get that flight path, once and for all.

scenes.label: *notload_M2
texts: ...But it was a little too soon to give up.
The plane was expected to fall in 20 minutes.
